ST. ANDREWS, Scotland (AP) — A brief look at the final round Sunday of the British Open at St. Andrews:VICTOR: Cameron Smith closed with an 8-under 64 for a one-shot victory and his first major.SPOILS: Smith won $2.5 million, the silver claret jug, a gold medal, an exemption to the British Open through 2053 (at age 60), and typically five-year exemptions into the Masters, the PGA Championship and the U.S. Open.SILVER MEDAL: Cameron Young (65) made a 15-foot eagle on the last hole to finish second.PURPLE HEART: Rory McIlroy was trying to end eight years without a major. Tied for the lead with Viktor Hovland to start the final round, he hit every green in regulation and two-putted every hole. He made two birdies for a 70 and finished third.RECORD BOOKS: Smith finished at 20-under 268 for the lowest score ever in a British Open at St. Andrews. It matched the lowest score to par in any major championship.ADVERTISEMENTSHOT OF THE DAY: Smith was 90 feet away from the hole on the par-5 14th when he used his putter to roll it up a huge mound and let it feed down to tap-in range for his fifth consecutive birdie and the first time he was in the lead.ROUND OF THE DAY: Sam Burns and Smith each had 64. For Smith, the 64 was the lowest final round by an Open champion at St. Andrews.GolfBirdies dry up for Hovland in final round of British OpenKey hole from final round of the British OpenSmith rallies to beat McIlroy at British Open for 1st majorMcIlroy regrets cold putter as wait goes on for 5th majorKEY STATISTIC: Smith took only 11 putts in regulation over the final nine holes.NOTEWORTHY: Smith is fifth Australian to win the Open and the third to win it at St. Andrews, joining Peter Thomson and Kel Nagle.QUOTEWORTHY: “There’s a worthy winner right on the 18th green right now.” — Rory McIlroy as Cameron Smith was accepting the claret jug.NEXT YEAR: The Open returns to Royal Liverpool in 2023.___More AP golf: https://apnews.com/hub/golf and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports